# üìò Time & Space Complexity ‚Äî DSA Notes (Java)

> **Purpose:** Quick, interview‚Äëready reference for analyzing algorithm efficiency.

---

## 1. What is Time Complexity?

Time complexity describes how an algorithm‚Äôs **execution time grows with input size (n)**.

* Measures **growth rate**, not actual seconds
* Platform & machine independent

---

## 2. Why It Matters

* Choose the **right approach** for large inputs
* Compare **multiple solutions**
* Essential for **interviews & optimization**

---

## 3. Types of Time Complexity

* **Best Case:** Minimum time (rarely discussed)
* **Average Case:** Expected time (hard to compute)
* **Worst Case ‚≠ê:** Maximum time (**used in interviews**)

---

## 4. Big‚ÄëO Notation

Represents the **upper bound (worst case)** growth.

### Rules

* Ignore constants ‚Üí `O(2n) = O(n)`
* Ignore lower terms ‚Üí `O(n¬≤ + n) = O(n¬≤)`
* Focus on the **dominant term**

---

## 5. Common Complexities (MEMORIZE)

```
O(1) < O(log n) < O(n) < O(n log n) < O(n¬≤) < O(2‚Åø) < O(n!)
```

| Complexity | Meaning      | Example       |
| ---------- | ------------ | ------------- |
| O(1)       | Constant     | Array access  |
| O(log n)   | Logarithmic  | Binary search |
| O(n)       | Linear       | Single loop   |
| O(n log n) | Linearithmic | Merge sort    |
| O(n¬≤)      | Quadratic    | Nested loops  |
| O(2‚Åø)      | Exponential  | Subsets       |
| O(n!)      | Factorial    | Permutations  |

---

## 6. How to Calculate Time Complexity

### Single Loop

```java
for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {}
```

‚Üí **O(n)**

### Nested Loops

```java
for (int i = 0; i < n; i++)
  for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {}
```

‚Üí **O(n¬≤)**

### Logarithmic Loop

```java
for (int i = 1; i <= n; i *= 2) {}
```

‚Üí **O(log n)**

### Sequential Loops

```java
for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {}
for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {}
```

‚Üí **O(n)**

---

## 7. Conditionals

```java
if (cond) { // O(n)
} else { // O(1)
}
```

‚Üí Worst case = **O(n)**

---

## 8. Recursion Complexity

| Pattern   | Time     | Space        |
| --------- | -------- | ------------ |
| `f(n-1)`  | O(n)     | O(n) (stack) |
| `f(n/2)`  | O(log n) | O(log n)     |
| Two calls | O(2‚Åø)    | O(n)         |

---

## 9. Space Complexity

Space includes:

* Extra variables
* Data structures (arrays, maps)
* **Recursion stack**

---

## 10. Constraints ‚Üí Approach Mapping (INTERVIEW GOLD)

| n          | Preferred Complexity |
| ---------- | -------------------- |
| ‚â§ 10¬≥      | O(n¬≤)                |
| ‚â§ 10‚Åµ      | O(n log n)           |
| ‚â§ 10‚Å∂      | O(n)                 |
| Very large | O(log n)             |

---
I will try to write time and space complexity for every problem i practice.

